column5: Hi I've been a lurker for a couple of years but do contribute to other boards you may also browse as CHROMINATOR13 and RANGER13. You have the best community of anglers I've seen to date so great job. I hope to contribute a more often as I do fish myself fishing about 120 days a year and have for about 25 years.  Weekend was great participating in Fishing Week festvities and Toronto Island. Pike and Bass fishing was PHENOMINAL all weekend.  Bass all caught on Green Senkos and Northerns on White Spinnerbaits 3/4 oz double willow.       Rest of my Gallery  can be found here  I also have some articles I contribute, below being the latest.  http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content <http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=84&Itemid=71> &task=view&id=84&Itemid=71  http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content <http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content&task=category§ionid=6&id=55&Itemid=101> &task=category§ionid=6&id=55&Itemid=101  http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content <http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=32&Itemid=79> &task=view&id=32&Itemid=79  http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content <http://www.fishonlineca.com/new/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=37&Itemid=71> &task=view&id=37&Itemid=71  This is the site that links to my 2 Canadian Records:  http://www.canadian-sportfishing.com/Natio...ve_Release1.asp    This is a link to some other online photos-some of which are within Toronto Harbour/Islands from last couple of years.   http://www.esnips.com/web/marktarnawczyksPhotos
Great Hello you will have to post alot to get rid of the newbie title, for some strange resson l don't think this is a past time for you lol. Glad to learn from more people. Welcome aboard. Peace Ken
Impressive resume that's for sure!  Welcome to the board...I'm sure you'll have lots to contribute!
Welcome aboard, I'm ready to learn from your obvious expertise.  Cheers,
Somebodies watching you in the background of your Pike Pic Lol. Hes probably zooming right in on your fish, hanging it on his fridge,  and taking credit for it lol
Welcome to the board.  if i'm not mistaken you had a very good year in the credit river in 1991!!!  lovetofish
Oh yah..speedo man..might have been Fruit of the Loom..wasn't looking that close. I think the jumping fish woke him up. He was creepy.
welcome!  if you've been watching for a while, then you already know there are a lot of good people here.  take care doug
Welcome Aboard and thanks for the great report and pics! You will really have a blast here
LOL, THATS HILARIOUS!! He is actually standin there in his tighty whities!!!! That is creepy. Talk about ruining a fishin hole
hahahah thats too funny, buddy in the boat was taking your picture too, man those whities  hes wearing look like an ad for adult incontinent products nice fish by the way cheers
Welcome aboard Ranger, looks like you had a quality day on the water, I just mite be hitting the island this weekend for some bucket mouth and Pike action i certainly hope i do well.
Welcome Ranger.  I enjoyed your article on Rice Lake Walleye... will be going there in a couple of weeks and hope to catch some.
welcome aboard,,,always glad to see some seasoned angles joining our family!!!
Yup... Freakish...   I wont smear you in scat and call it sugar..  a simple welcome will suffice.  Enjoy the ride.  Gerritt.
Welcome and nice report! The bass fishing should really pick up there now, fishing from a boat is way better around the islands.  cheers,  ehg
